JOHANNESBURG – Steinhoff wants shareholder Christo Wiese to reimburse the company for two payments made to him in 2017. The retailer says the payments didn’t follow proper governance and disclosure processes. READ: How Steinhoff execs cooked the books It says the deals were agreed to in the weeks leading up to the emergence of financial irregularities that have wiped more than 90 percent off the value of the global retailer. The company hired auditors PWC to investigate the accounting scandal. eNCA